{"key":"processedPost-7084545","value":{"id":7084545,"first":7084089,"last":7084545,"when":1182646224,"utime":"06/24/07 03:50 AM","content":"Use the fruit.  With multispore inoculation, often several strains are active in the same jar/substrate.  By cloning a mushroom fruit body, you're sure to be getting tertiary mycelium, which is the fruiting type.  Clone a young, rapidly growing pin for best results.  As said, if you clone from a cluster, the offspring will tend to form clusters, and if you clone an individual fruit, the offspring will also follow suit.<br />RR","title":"Re: cloning question...mycelium vs. single mushroom","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}